{
  "texts": [
    "This metric provides valuable insights into the computational efficiency and latency of healthcare chatbots, aiding in their optimization for faster and more efficient response times.",
    "The Token Limit metric evaluates the performance of chatbots, focusing on the number of tokens used in multi-turn interactions.",
    "The number of tokens significantly impacts the word count in a query and the computational resources required during inference.",
    "As the number of tokens increases, the memory and computation needed also increase 63, leading to higher latency and reduced usability.",
    "The Number of Parameters of the LLM model is a widely used metric that signifies the model's size and complexity."
  ]
}